      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIRESTRIKE (9) is a four-year-old gelding by top sire Bettors Delight on debut. Hails from a leading yard in Luke McCarthy and while he cops a wide draw he has looked talented in winning his two trials at this circuit and distance, both by big margins. WARRAWEES SHOUT (1) performed admirably from a second row draw last time out, making up plenty of ground to be beaten less than 2m into third at Wagga. Should have no excuses from the ace draw. TILLY DEEVINNE (10) started a hot favourite last week but it all went wrong when she broke in the score up and then had to work. Still has plenty to learn and starts from the outside but suspect there is ability there if the penny drops. IM JUST SAYIN (3) is heading the right way, improving last time out when she came from this barrier to miss narrowly when second over this distance at Newcastle.",
